column3: Description
Repair/repaint/replace all deteriorated bathroom cabinets.
Caulk perimeter of tub/shower at floor/flooring where caulking/grout is deteriorated/missing. Remove all old/deteriorated caulking at floor/flooring
Caulk perimeter of tub/shower at enclosure walls where caulking/grout is deteiorating/missing.  Remove all old/deteriorated caulking/grout at enclosure walls.
Caulk perimeter of sink at rim/cabinet top where caulking/grout is deteriorated/missing.  Perimeter of sink must be watertight.
Caulk gap between wall and sink/cabinet top behind sink. Remove all old/deteriorated caulking/grout. Perimeter of wall behind sink must be watertight.
Provide the following number of common bathroom facilities as directed:
Provide/replace bathroom door hardware/knob.
Repair/unclog specified drain.
Replace all deteriorated bathroom floor coverings.
Unclog drain
Secure bathtub overflow to prevent leakage.
Resurface/re-glaze tub where surface is deteriorated. Remove any rust on surface of tub. Use proper materials/compounds for resurfacing/re-glazing tub.
Repair/replace faulty/missing fixtures and/or hardware at tub/shower.
Replace all deteriorated/missing bathroom tiles.
Bathroom sink.
Repair/replace faucet/controls at bathroom sink.
Repair/unclog bathroom sink drain.
Resurface/re-glaze bathroom sink where surface is deteriorated.  Remove any rust on surface of sink. Use proper materials/compounds for resurfacing/re-glazing sink.
Secure bathroom sink to wall. Ensure that sink is properly supported where needed.
Repair/replace bathroom shower door and/or associated hardware.

Walls around shower/tub shall have smooth, hard nonabsorbent surfaces made of Portland cement, concrete, ceramic tile or other smooth, hard nonabsorbent surfaces extending to a height of seventy inches and to no less than two feet away from the edge of the tub/shower enclosure.
Repair toilet to flush properly.  Replace all deteriorated/missing components.
Secure toilet base to floor.
Replace deteriorated toilet seat and/or tank lid.
Caulk around toilet base.
Repair/Provide bathroom ventilation fan.  Obtain any required permits and inspections.
Repair/Provide bathroom ventilation fan.  Obtain any required permits and inspections.
Repair/Provide bathroom ventilation fan.  Obtain any required permits and inspections.
Repair/Resurface/Repaint bathroom wall(s) where deteriorated/damaged, where holes exist, and/or where paint is peeling/missing.
Repair/provide bathroom wall coving where deteriorated/peeling/missing.
Repair/Replace/Repaint all deteriorated bathroom ceilings.
Provide openable bathroom window with a minimum opening of 1.5 square feet or 1/20 of room area, whichever is greater. Replace glass as needed.
Repair/Replace/Repaint bathroom wall coving where deteriorated/damaged, where paint is peeling/missing, and/or where coving is coming away from bathroom wall(s).
Provide openable bathroom window for ventilation.
Repair/resurface/repaint all deteriorated bathroom door(s).
Repair/resurface/repaint deteriorated balcony/landing.
Repair/resurface/repaint deteriorated guardrails; loose/broken components.
Repair/replace termite damaged and decayed wood.
Provide adequate clean supply of sheets. pillow cases, blankets/comforters.  Mattresses shall be kept in good condition free from filth, urine, lice, bedbugs or other insects.
Provide an on premises caretaker for this complex of 16 units or more.
Repair/replace carpeting at common hallway.
Repair/replace deteriorated unit carpeting.

The building lacks the required carbon monoxide alarms. Install carbon monoxide alarms outside of each sleeping area in the immediate vicinity of the bedrooms and on every level of the dwelling unit. The alarms may be powered by battery or building wiring.
The building lacks the required smoke detectors. Install smoke detectors in the bedrooms and hallways. The detectors maybe powered by battery or building wiring.
Discontinue using as a cooking area any room that is not designed and intended for use as a kitchen.
Remove dangerous articles from exterior of premises as directed.
Repair/remove/reinstall closet door(s).
Repair deteriorated entry door framing and/or jamb.
Repair/Repaint/Weatherproof exterior door.
Repair/replace deteriorated entry door threshold to provide a proper seal when closed.
Repair/replace deteriorated/non-operational entry door lock/knob.
Repair/Replace/Provide approved security locking mechanism for entry door(s). (Note: Do not install deadbolt locks that are keyed on both sides - use only those with thumb latches on entry doors).
Install weather stripping materials around entry door(s) to exclude rodents.
Properly install weather strip at base of entry door(s) and along sides of door frame to exclude rain water.
Repair/resurface/repaint interior door(s).
Repair or replace deteriorated door.
Repair/Replace/Provide approved security locking mechanism for entry door(s).
Rodent proof entry door.
Properly weather strip entry door(s) to exclude rain water.
Grade exterior surfaces to direct water away from buildings and prevent accumulation of water.
Check electrical circuit breakers for proper operation.
Discontinue using cord wiring.
Repair/replace all missing or damaged electrical outlet and switch plates.
Repair/replace all deteriorated/broken/missing light fixtures.
Repair/replace all deteriorated electrical outlets/switches.
Repair/Replace all deteriorated electrical outlets/switches.
Repair all holes on the exterior of the building.
Repair/repaint deteriorated gas meter enclosure and/or doors.
Repair/repaint deteriorated electric meter enclosure and/or doors.
Repair/repaint/seal exterior wood trim/surfaces where damaged and/or where paint is peeling/missing.
Replace/secure all deteriorated/missing exterior siding.
Repair/repaint deteriorated/missing exterior stucco.

All properties shall be posted with the number or numbers designated for the principal entrance or entrances of a building. Install address numbers, not less than three inches in height, at the principal entrance of the building in plain view from the public right-of-way.
Discarded furniture and household items shall not be stored in yard areas. Remove the discarded furniture and/or household items stored or kept in the yard areas.
Trash and garbage cans cannot be stored in front or side yards visible from public streets.  Remove the trash cans and/or trash bins stored or kept in yard areas visible from public streets.
There is graffiti painted on the premises.  Remove all graffiti from the premises

It shall be the duty of responsible person(s) to prevent accumulation and storage of abandoned, wrecked, dismantled, or inoperative vehicles or parts thereof, except for those vehicles or parts thereof exempted pursuant to Long Beach Municipal Code Section 10.46.030.  Remove all inoperative vehicles or vehicle parts from the property or bring vehicle(s) to an operative condition including current registration status.

Temporary electrical power and lighting installations shall be permitted for a period not to exceed 90 days for holiday decorative lighting and similar purposes.  Remove all temporary power/lighting installations.
Repair deteriorated fencing and/or gate(s).
Repair/replace all damaged/missing floor coverings throughout the dwelling.
Repair/replace deteriorated sub-floor and/or supports as directed and obtain necessary permits and inspections.
Remove doorway from garage to sleeping area in an approved manner.
Repair/replace missing or deteriorated garage door.

Seal all holes at garage walls/ceiling/floor where garages are attached to residential units to prevent vermin/rodent entry into units.  All holes greater than 1/4 inch must be sealed, including holes at pipe penetrations.
Repair gas leak at appliance/fitting.  Contact Long Beach Gas Department to check appliance before returning to service.

Obtain all required permits and inspections and provide approved unit heater capable of heating unit to 70 degrees Fahrenheit, measured three feet above the floor.  NOTE: Space heaters are not approved for permanent use.

Obtain all required permits and inspections and provide approved unit heater capable of heating unit to 70 degrees Fahrenheit, measured three feet above the floor.  A temporary heater must be provided during winter months if a permanent heater cannot be repaired or replaced in a timely manner.
Repair/resurface/repaint all deteriorated interior walls and ceiling areas.
Repair/Replace deteriorated kitchen cabinet and/or doors.
Repair/replace deteriorated kitchen drawers.
Repair/replace all deteriorated kitchen counters and/or edge banding.
Repair/replace/remove dishwasher.
Unclog kitchen sink drain.
Repair/replace leaking/inoperable kitchen faucet hardware.
Repair/replace deteriorated/missing kitchen floor covering.
Repair/replace/remove garbage disposal.
Repair/replace/remove refrigerator.
Seal/caulk kitchen counter top at sink to prevent water intrusion/damage at kitchen walls/floors/cabinet.
Seal/caulk perimeter/rim of kitchen sink. Caulking/grout must be watertight, smooth and cleanable. Remove old/deteriorated caulking/grout.
Seal around kitchen faucet to prevent water leaks.
Repair leaking plumbing under kitchen sink.
Repair/reglaze kitchen sink.
Provide a kitchen sink with drain boards.
Tenant must clean kitchen stove.
Repair and/or repaint kitchen walls/ceiling where damaged/deteriorated or where paint is peeling/missing.  Paint all areas of walls/ceiling that are unpainted.
Repair/replace/repaint damaged/deteriorated wall/base/doors of cabinet under kitchen sink, including holes around pipe penetrations.
Provide/maintain/repair mechanical ventilation for fuel burning appliance(s).  Obtain any required permits and inspections.
Repair/replace inoperative/faulty stove, which may cause fire hazard.
Repair/replace inoperative/faulty stove, which may cause fire hazard.
Repair/replace inoperative/faulty stove, which may cause fire hazard.

Presumed lead base paint or lead paint hazards, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located.

Eliminate chipping and peeling paint, which is presumed lead base paint or lead paint hazards, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located, associated with an elevated blood level equal to or greater than 10 micrograms per deciliter.

Eliminate excessive chipping and peeling paint, which is lead base paint or lead paint hazards, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or premises on which it is located.

Eliminate chipping and peeling paint, which is lead base paint or lead paint hazards, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located, associated with an elevated blood level equal to or greater than 10 micrograms per deciliter.

Eliminate lead base paint or lead paint hazards, specifically lead-contaminated dust, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located.

Eliminate lead base paint or lead paint hazards, specifically lead-contaminated soil, using Lead Safe Work Practices, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located.

Utilize Lead Safe Work Practices in renovation(s) or routine maintenance activities and abate any lead hazard(s) and/or cease and desist disturbance of lead base paint without containment, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located - HS 17920.10(c)  Any construction activity that is creating or has created a lead hazard is a violation that shall be an infraction punishable by a fine not to exceed one thousand dollars ($1000) - HS 105256.

Utilize Lead Safe Work Practices in renovation(s) or routine maintenance activities and abate any lead hazard(s) and/or cease and desist disturbance of lead base paint without containment, in any building or portion thereof including any dwelling unit, guestroom, or suite of rooms, or portion thereof, or the premises on which it is located, associated with an elevated blood level equal to or greater than 10 micrograms per deciliter - HS 17920.10(c), HS 17920.10(d)  Any construction activity that is creating or has created a lead hazard is a violation that shall be an infraction punishable by a fine not to exceed one thousand dollars ($1000) - HS 105256.
Provide working lighting in hallways, stairways and exit balconies. Repair/Provide fixtures as directed. Ensure that dark areas are readily illuminated during and after dusk/nightfall.
Replace all damaged or missing light fixtures with approved fixtures.
Repair/replace inoperative light fixtures and outlets.
Repair/provide wall switch to control light fixtures.
Route dryer exhaust to exterior of building. Maintain dryer duct free of accumulated lint on a regular basis.
Repair/Repaint all deteriorated laundry room walls and/or ceilings.  Seal all holes, including holes at pipe penetrations, and paint all unpainted surfaces.
Provide adequate ventilation as directed via window or exhaust fan.  Obtain any required permits and inspections.
Properly discharge wastewater into the sanitary sewer system. Discontinue discharging wastewater to the street/alley/soil.

Whenever necessary to make an inspection to enforce any of the provisions of this title, or whenever the building official or his authorized representative has reasonable cause to believe that there exists in any building or upon any condition or code violation which makes such building or premises substandard, unsafe, dangerous or hazardous, the building official or his authorized representative may enter such building or premises at all reasonable times to inspect the same or to perform any duty imposed. PROPERTY OWNER:  Take the following corrective action in conjunction with any other corrective actions in this Notice: PROVIDE ACCESS TO THE BUILDING OFFICIAL FOR INSPECTIONS.

Remove mold/mildew at unit/room and correct condition causing mold growth.  Drywall should be replaced when mold has covered the surface. Inadequate sanitation shall include any visible or otherwise demonstrable mold growth, excluding the presence of molds that is caused by inappropriate housekeeping practices or improper use of natural or mechanical ventilation.

No person may establish or maintain a beehive at a distance less than one hundred feet from a dwelling, except the dwelling occupied by the person establishing or maintaining the beehive. Beehives must be at least 100 feet from a public way.

LBMC 6.24.010 Remove beehive(s) and keep at a distance less than one hundred feet (100) from a dwelling, except the dwelling occupied by the person establishing or maintaining the beehive.  Maintain beehive(s) at least 100 feet away from any public way/path and at least an elevation of 10 feet above the ground.  Note: A beehive means any box, container, structure, chamber or shelter within which bees have taken possession.  All beekeeping operations shall be registered with the Los Angeles County Department of Agricultural Commissioner- LBMC 6.24.010.

No person shall keep any live fowl in a coop that is less than twice as large in floor space or standing room as the total size of all live fowl in the coop. The coop must be of a height such that each fowl is able to stand in a natural erect position.
No person shall keep or maintain or cause to be kept or maintained any crowing fowl. Remove crowing fowl from property.

No person shall keep or maintain more than a total of twenty (20) live fowl or any combination of such animals on any lot or parcel of land within the city. Note: One live fowl may be kept or maintained as a pet on any lot or parcel of land within the city, provided that the pen, coop or other such enclosure for any such pet fowl shall be no less than twenty feet (20') from any structure designed or used for human habitation.

Wherever live fowl are permitted to be kept or maintained in the city, no person, so keeping or maintaining such fowl shall fail at any time to keep the coops, pens or yards when such fowl are enclosed in a clean and sanitary condition nor shall fail to remove the manure or other debris from such enclosures daily.

No person shall keep or maintain any live fowl within the city less than fifty feet (50') from any single family or two family dwelling or less than 100 feet (100') from any hotel or dwelling occupied by , or designed for the occupancy of three or more families. Note: One live fowl may be kept or maintained as a pet on any lot or parcel of land within the city, provided that the pen, coop or other such enclosure for any such pet fowl shall be no less than twenty fee (20') from any structure designed or used for human habitation.
No person shall allow any fowl owned or controlled by such person to run at large.
Eliminate from the premises any infestation or harboring of insects or other vermin that may be a danger to the public health.
Pigeon coops shall be maintained in a clean and sanitary condition.

Pigeon coops must be at least thirty-five feet (35') from the owner's dwelling and not less than fifty feet (50') from any other dwelling, and not less than one hundred feet (100') from any multiple unit dwelling.
Provide required permit or remove from the premises any live pigeons.

Pigeon coops must be twice as large in floor space or standing room as the total size of all live pigeons in the coop.  The space must be of a sufficient height so as to permit each pigeon to stand in a natural erect position.

All feed shall be stored in containers which offer protection against rodents and insects; pigeon manure and other waste material arising from their maintenance shall be removed from the permittee's premises at least once per week.
No person shall keep or maintain on any lot or parcel of land more than forty (40) live pigeons.
Discontinue overcrowding in the efficiency units specified. (See inspector comments for allowable number of occupants per available area.)
Discontinue overcrowding in unit(s) specified. (See Inspector comments for allowable number of occupants per available area.)
Provide/secure cap on open sewer cleanout and repair all plumbing problems causing sewage flow/backup.
Repair deteriorated and/or clogged exterior plumbing.
Repair/Replace all plumbing deficiencies.
Repair/Replace deteriorated porches and/or steps.
Repair/Replace deteriorated porch roof covering.
Repair/repaint/seal all wood porch components where deteriorated.
Discontinue using rooms with the dimension of less than 7 feet by 10 feet or a ceiling height of less than 7 feet as habitable.
Take immediate action to repair/replace roof to be watertight.
Take immediate action to repair/replace roof to be watertight.
Remove trash/debris from roof areas.

Provide trash facilities adequate enough to handle trash load of tenants on a calendar week basis. Ensure that all containers have closeable lids and are kept closed at all times. Note: Increased frequency of pick up and/or additional containers may be required to accomplish this task.

Remove animal fecal material from premises on a daily basis, placing it in a sealed plastic bag for disposal with the regular trash. Wash down or mop urine with a small amount of diluted sanitizer to eliminate odor. Do not hose off balconies onto other balconies, street, alley, or common areas.
Remove and replace, or immediately clean and sanitize, sewage soaked carpeting; take all necessary actions to dry carpet rapidly.
Sanitize trash facilities on a routine basis to prevent potential insect/rodent harborage.
Take immediate action to sanitize sewage contaminated areas as directed.
Trim all overgrown foliage/lawns/shrubs at property to prevent vermin/rodent harborage or entrance to units/buildings.
Sanitize sewage soaked ground and remove waste material as directed. Do not allow sewage and/or sanitizer to flow off property or into streets, gutters, or storm drains.
Remove scattered trash, castoff items and debris around premises.
Trim trees/shrubs to no less than 18 inches from building and roof to prevent rodent entrance to building(s).
Provide mosquito proof screen for sliding glass entry door.
Provide mosquito proof screens on all openable windows.

Discontinue using any of the following portions of a building as a sleeping space: kitchen, hallway, water closet, bathroom, cellar, garage or any area in which sleeping may be dangerous to life or health.
Repair/repaint/secure deteriorated exterior stairway.
Repair/repaint deteriorated stair landings as directed.  Obtain all required permits and inspections.
Repair/repaint all deteriorated handrails and/or guardrails.
Repair/replace all deteriorated interior staircase component(s)
The rise and run of the steps/stairs do not comply with code requirements. Reconstruct the steps/stairs to conform to minimum code requirements. Please obtain all required building permit.
Provide 1/4-inch hardware mesh on all attic vents to prevent rodent entry. Use 1/8-inch hardware mesh to eliminate potential for bee hives.
Provide 1/4-inch hardware mesh on all foundation vent openings for rodent proofing
Effectively exterminate for fleas.

Exterminate cockroaches at all units where infestation is present.  Seal all cracks, gaps, and holes in walls, floors, and cupboards, and around piping insertions.  Remove or paint over all spotting in unit.  Provide pest control service to all infested units and surrounding units sharing common floors, ceilings, and walls with infested units.  NOTE:  Treatment is most effective when all units are treated on the same day, treatment is repeated to target hatching young in two weeks or every two weeks until infestation is removed.
Exterminate rodents at unit/building.  Remove all rodent droppings. Weather strip entry doors, and seal all holes at walls, floors and ceilings.

Effectively exterminate for bed bugs using a professional pest control company.  Inspect/monitor/treat all surrounding units in building that share common walls, floors, and ceilings with all infected units.
Provide natural ventilation in the unit equal to one twentieth of the floor area in each habitable room.

Provide water service to this occupied complex.  All plumbing fixtures shall be connected to an approved system of water supply and provided with hot and cold running water necessary for its normal operation.
Replace deteriorated water heater.  Obtain all required inspections and permits.  Properly vent gas water heater. Strap or secure water heater to protect from earthquake hazards.
Provide hot water under pressure to this complex/unit to a temperature of at least 110 degrees Fahrenheit.

Provide water service to this occupied complex.  All plumbing fixtures shall be connected to an approved system of water supply and provided with hot and cold running water necessary for its normal operation - LBMC 18.40.010, UHC 505.4.
Repair/Replace all deteriorated and/or damaged window frames.
Replace all broken window glass.

Provide the required levels of natural light and ventilation in all habitable rooms. Glazed exterior window area must be a minimum of 10 square feet or 1/10 of floor area, whichever is larger. Windows must be openable to the exterior of the building.
Repair/replace all inoperative sash balances on openable windows to operate correctly. Windows must be openable to the exterior of the building and must be closeable.
Repair/replace windows to a weather tight condition.

Provide the required natural light and ventilation in all habitable rooms.  Glazed exterior window area to be a minimum of 10 square feet or 1/10 of floor area, whichever is larger.  Openable exterior opening to be a minimum of 5 square feet of 1/20 of floor area, whichever is greater - LBMC 18.40.010, UBC 1203.3.
Repair/Replace all inoperable sash balances on openable windows to be operable.
Provide mosquito proof screens on all openable windows.
Repair/Replace all windows to a weathertight condition.
Repair and repaint all deteriorated window frames/components/surfaces.

There are metal bars over the bedroom emergency escape windows. Remove the bars or provide an emergency release mechanism on the emergency escape window of each bedroom.                                                                                     Security bars in the bedroom window is missing the emergency release mechanism. Provide required emergency release mechanism and obtain all necessary building permit.
Provide smooth, trip free surfaces at all walkways.
